TCF Canada Prep — dual-licence notice
========================================

This repository contains two kinds of work, licensed differently:

1. **Content** — every file under `content/`, the `ROADMAP.md`, and any text
   destined for the learner (including model answers, transcripts, vocabulary
   lists, mock exams, and cheatsheets) — is licensed under the
   **Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 4.0 International (CC-BY-SA-4.0)**.
   See `LICENSE-CONTENT.txt`.

2. **Software / tooling** — every file under `tools/`, `tests/`, `latex/`,
   `mkdocs.yml`, `pyproject.toml`, build scripts, and CI workflows — is
   licensed under the **MIT License**. See `LICENSE-TOOLS.txt`.

Authentic-text snippets paraphrased from third-party sources (Le Monde,
Radio-Canada, Le Devoir, La Presse, France Culture, RFI Savoirs, TV5MONDE
Apprendre, etc.) are cited in `references.bib` and used under fair-use /
short-quotation provisions. None are reproduced in extenso. If you are a
rights holder and a citation needs adjustment, please open an issue.

The contents of `00_MASTER_PROMPT.md`, `01_PROJECT_CONTEXT.md`, and the
`02_PHASE_*` through `09_PHASE_*` files are the prompt bundle authored by
the project initiator and are released under CC-BY-SA-4.0.
